# Standard button icons

Use Lucide (`@lucide/vue`) icons consistently for the same actions across the app. Place the icon before the label; Button already provides `gap-2` and default SVG sizing.

| Action                   | Icon        | Notes                            |
| ------------------------ | ----------- | -------------------------------- |
| Back / cancel navigation | `ArrowLeft` | Outline back links               |
| Create / add             | `Plus`      | Create submit + index “new” CTAs |
| Save / update            | `Save`      | Edit form submit                 |
| Edit                     | `Pencil`    | Row/menu edit actions            |
| Users / members          | `Users`     | Navigate to users                |
| Delete / remove          | `Trash2`    | Destructive remove actions       |

## Example

```vue
<Button type="submit">
  <Save class="h-4 w-4" />
  {{ t('common.save') }}
</Button>
```

Do not mix synonyms (e.g. `ChevronLeft` for back, `Check` for save) unless the existing design system already requires it for that surface.
